    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix sync period checking in vnf_sync functions\n\n### Summary\nThe vnf_sync and vnf_nr_sync functions in the Open-nFAPI VNF implementation incorrectly validated synchronization periods using a bitwise AND operation with a mask. This approach only works when the period is a power of 2, causing incorrect behavior when periods are other values.\n\nThe issue manifested as VNFs not sending DL_NODE_SYNC messages at the expected intervals, leading to synchronization problems between VNF and PNF. The root cause was using `(value & (period-1)) == 0` to check if `value` is a multiple of `period`, which is only valid for powers of 2.\n\nThis fix changes the validation to use the modulo operator directly: `(value % period) == 0`, which works correctly for any period value.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/vnf/src/vnf_p7.c`: \n  - Modified vnf_sync() to use modulo operator instead of bitwise AND for period checking\n  - Modified vnf_nr_sync() to use modulo operator instead of bitwise AND for period checking\n  - Changed variable names from dl_sync_period_mask to dl_sync_period for clarity\n"
}